    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'm on the v0.5.0 nightly (macOS 11.1, Terminal) and notice that large pop-up windows still get truncated at the right edge of the terminal window. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"584\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-01-15 at 21 44 59\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20085376/104821069-9d472e00-5839-11eb-95bb-70305718e84a.png\">\r\n\r\nAs far as I understood, when the popup does not fit width-wise, the expected behaviour is that the pop-up should move to the left of the cursor (see also #13085 ). \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
